annotationA: Discs overgrown protein kinase; Involved in circadian rhythms, viability and molecular oscillations of the clock genes period (per) and timeless (tim). Dbt reduces the stability and thus the accumulation of monomeric per proteins, probably through phosphorylation. No evident circadian oscillation is detected in head. Together with CkIalpha, regulates processing of ci by phosphorylating it which promotes its binding to slmb, the F-box recognition component of the SCF(slmb) E3 ubiquitin-protein ligase; Belongs to the protein kinase superfamily. annotationB: Regulatory particle triple-A ATPase 4 (Rpt4) is the 19S proteasomal ATPase, which is a component of the 26S proteosome complex. Rpt4 localizes to the nucleolus and participates in regulating rRNA transcription. Rpt4 physically interacts with the BHD tumor suppressor
